<TEXT>
art dealer peg goldberg who battled 
cyprus over ownership of four 6thcentury mosaics has lost her bid 
for reelection as hamilton county commissioner 
with 60 of 116 precincts reporting in tuesdays republican 
primary challenger william r karns had 5846 votes or 66 
percent to goldbergs 3017 or 34 percent in heavily republican 
hamilton county winning the primary is tantamount to victory 
goldberg bought the mosaics for 12 million from a turkish 
national living in switzerland the church and the republic of 
cyprus sued her last year saying the mosaics were national 
treasures that were stolen from a church in turkishcontrolled 
northern cyprus 
she is appealing a federal judges order to return the byzantine 
mosaics to the autocephalous greek orthodox church of cyprus the 
us 7th circuit court of appeals in chicago has not yet ruled on 
the case 
goldberg had said in february she would not run for reelection 
until her appeals were exhausted however she later changed her 
position 
she ran on a platform calling for a zoning plan for all of the 
county a comprehensive road and drainage program and a new 
judicial center 
karns is chairman of the board of karns inc a carmel concrete 
company 
