<TEXT>
the federal election commission is 
investigating three related arizona companies and at least two of 
their officers for allegedly making illegal donations to the 
republican party and bush presidential campaign 
the agencys actions were disclosed in documents filed monday in 
us district court in phoenix seeking a court order to force the 
companies to surrender certain financial records the agency as a 
rule refuses to comment on current investigations 
the fecs filing said the investigation began late last year and 
that a former employee told the agency the two officers were 
reimbursed with corporate funds after making donations to the gop 
and bush campaign the agency also said corporate letterhead and 
postage may have been used to solicit donations on behalf of the 
bush campaign 
information suggests that respondents made corporate 
contributions to federal candidates disguised as contributions 
made in other names and used corporate funds to solicit 
contributions to federal candidates the fec said 
the companies all with headquarters at the same address in 
scottsdale ariz are the national association of real estate 
appraisers the national association of review appraisers and 
mortgage underwriters and the international association managers 
individuals named in the complaint are robert johnson executive 
director of the groups and e kenneth twichell managing director 
of the national association of real estate appraisers 
johnson in a telephone interview denied any wrongdoing and 
said he had provided fec attorneys all requested documents 
johnson said he never reimbursed himself twichell or any other 
employees for political donations or used corporate letterhead for 
fundraising he said fec lawyers had refused to provide him with 
any evidence of the allegations or name the former employee who 
made the allegations 
i believe this investigation is bordering on harassment he 
said 
the fec the court papers say voted unanimously that there was 
reason to believe johnson and twichell were reimbursed with 
corporate funds after making political donations that would 
violate laws prohibiting corporate donations and making 
contributions in the name of another 
the court papers also allege that twichell sent at least one and 
possibly several letters to members of the organizations soliciting 
donations for the bush campaign using corporate letterhead and 
postage for such a campaign would violate prohibitions against 
corporate expenses or donations on behalf of federal candidates 
twichell is out of the country his office said tuesday 
