<TEXT>
a botched execution that caused flames 
to shoot from the head of an inmate in an electric chair was caused 
by a synthetic sponge gov bob martinez said 
the malfunction occurred because two maintenance workers had 
substituted a synthetic sponge for the natural sponge that serves 
as a conduit for electrical current applied to the prisoners head 
martinez said tuesday the synthetic sponge didnt work properly 
he said 
flames smoke and sparks shot 3 to 6 inches above the head of 
jessie tafero as authorities administered three 2000volt shocks 
to the convicted copkiller on friday 
the governor said the maintenance workers took it upon 
themselves to replace what they thought to be a wornout sponge 
and didnt realize there is a different chemical reaction by virtue 
of substituting a synthetic sponge for a natural sponge 
a report from corrections secretary richard dugger said tafero 
died immediately the attending physicians report indicated that 
at the least the condemned man was knocked unconscious by the jolt 
there is no way to apply 2000 volts directly to someones 
brain without killing them instantly said dugger who has 
witnessed 16 executions they are never conscious of what 
happens 
dugger in a report requested by the governor said prison 
officials had conducted a test using a household toaster that 
confirmed the synthetic sponge caused the problem 
although the sponge was only in the toaster for ten seconds it 
produced a large amount of smoke and reduced in size by 
approximately twothirds the report said 
taferos attorney mark olive of atlanta and the florida 
clearinghouse on criminal justice called the execution torture 
