<TEXT>
president fw de klerk of south africa arrived 
here today on the first stop of an 18day european tour viewed by 
his government as a major step toward ending decades of 
international isolation 
buoyed by a breakthrough in blackwhite negotiations at home de 
klerk plans to meet with presidents and prime ministers in nine 
west european countries the most extensive trip by a south 
african leader since the governing national party took power in 
1948 
in his talks with european leaders de klerk is likely to urge 
an easing of economic sanctions imposed on his country and to seek 
support for his initiative to negotiate a political settlement with 
the black majority 
he is to confer thursday with president francois mitterrand who 
shunned pw botha de klerks predecessor when botha came to 
france to visit the graves of south african soldiers killed in the 
two world wars 
no senior french official was at orly airport to greet de klerk 
who was met by a foreign ministry representative and a military 
honor guard 
de klerk had no public events scheduled today but planned a news 
conference thursday evening after meetings with mitterrand and 
premier michel rocard 
de klerk reportedly was to have lunch thursday with prominent 
business leaders from across france south africas sixth largest 
trading partner despite its observance of limited european 
community economic sanctions 
mitterrand decided to invite de klerk after the south african 
leader made moves toward reform in february including the release 
of jailed south african black leader nelson mandela and the 
legalization of antiapartheid groups 
last week de klerk and a delegation of african national 
congress officials led by mandela agreed to work together to end 
political violence and clear the way for formal negotiations on a 
new postapartheid constitution that would end the 5 million white 
minoritys monopoly on power 
it is wonderful to go to europe with the knowledge that south 
africa is busy taking its rightful place in the international 
community de klerk told reporters before his departure from 
johannesburg late tuesday 
en route he conferred briefly with president felix 
houphouetboigny of the ivory coast during a refueling stop in 
abidjan the capital of the west african country no details were 
available on their meeting 
south africas staterun television quoted a senior government 
source as saying the european trip represented a concerted effort 
to pull south africa from the morass the country has found itself 
in the report said the visit is of the utmost importance 
to south africa 
after france de klerk will visit belgium italy west germany 
britain spain switzerland greece and portugal 
among his hosts will be british prime minister margaret 
thatcher king juan carlos of spain and west german chancellor 
helmut kohl 
frances relations with south africa have been marked by several 
peculiarities 
in the 1970s french authorities incurred international 
criticism for nurturing a major arms trade with south africa 
including the sale of the mirage fighter planes the backbone of 
south africas air force 
since mitterrand became president in 1981 france has stayed in 
step with other european community members in imposing selective 
sanctions but has never been a vocal advocate of escalating such 
embargoes in some parisian liquor stores south african wines are 
displayed in windows alongside local vintages 
johnny clegg the white leader of a multiracial antiapartheid 
south african rock n roll group is more of a superstar in france 
than anywhere outside his home country yet the antiapartheid 
movement in france is less of a force than its counterparts in 
britain the netherlands and scandinavia 
