stalins conduct of the war and expressed hope that his summit 
meeting in washington with president bush at months end will lead 
to further disarmament and an easing of world tensions 
the soviet leader smiled waved and raised his clasped hands as 
he led the leadership onto the reviewing stand for the second time 
in eight days leaving the stand at the end of the parade he 
raised a bouquet of red and white flowers to the applause of the 
diplomatic corps that gathered to watch 
war veterans bedecked with rows of glistening medals marched in 
columns between military bands soldiers sailors paratroopers 
and kgb border guards 
the motorized portion of the parade opened with the rumble and 
smoke of twodozen vintage t34 tanks the tank was first produced 
in 1943 and helped push back the nazis from deep inside soviet 
territory 
overall the soviets showed 18 pieces of modern equipment 
