the recording industry today unveiled a 
uniform voluntary parental warning label for albums that might 
contain explicit lyrics 
jay berman president of the recording industry association of 
america told a news conference that the blackandwhite label will 
appear on the lower righthand corner of possiblyobjectionable 
records cassettes and compact discs reaching retail stores 
starting in july 
