<TEXT>
soviet world war ii veterans wednesday celebrated 
their defeat of the nazis 45 years ago but worried that a reunited 
germany could once again threaten their homeland 
a senior naval officer thought a reunified germany so repulsive 
he responded angrily when asked about the issue i killed germans 
then and if i have to ill kill them again he refused to give 
his name and stormed off 
thousands of grayhaired veterans took advantage of bright 
spring weather to don their uniforms pin on their medals and 
gather in parks to recall the conflict they call the great war for 
the fatherland 
it was their first victory day celebration since east germanys 
hardline communist leader erich honecker was swept from power the 
berlin wall was opened and negotiations began on reuniting east and 
west germany 
most of the halfdozen veterans interviewed in sverdlov square 
outside the bolshoi theater after an official military parade in 
nearby red square said they would tolerate a reunited germany only 
if it were neutral belonging neither to the nato nor warsaw pact 
military alliances 
