rival christian forces escalated their 
battle wednesday for control of a strategic stretch of coastline 
killing 20 people and wounding 41 in fierce shelling duels police 
said 
the barrages came after rebel gen michel aoun threatened to 
attack ships using ports controlled by his rival samir geageas 
lebanese forces militia 
aoun backed up his threat by using howitzer batteries deployed 
in mountains northeast of beirut to shell almost the entire length 
of the christian enclaves 28mile mediterranean coastline in an 
effort to block geageas supply lines a police spokesman said 
police said aouns gunners were shelling ports controlled by the 
