maintains his shelling for 10 years 
smoke billowed from east beiruts ashrafiyeh district a geagea 
stronghold and the pinewoods of the metn mountains northeast of 
beirut where aouns troops are entrenched 
the thuds of exploding shells echoed across beirut as radio 
stations interrupted regular programming to blare appeals from 
hospitals for blood donations to cope with the influx of casualties 
beiruts moslem sector has not been involved in the christian 
fighting about 400000 of the christian enclaves 1 million 
population have fled the fighting mainly to safer areas in 
predominantly moslem sectors of the nation 
in another development lebanese president elias hrawi and prime 
minister salim hoss drove to the syrian capital of damascus for 
talks with president hafez assad on ways of implementing a peace 
plan to end lebanons 15yearold civil war 
aoun has rejected the arab leaguebrokered peace accord 
endorsed by lebanons parliament in the saudi arabian resort of 
taif in october because it does not guarantee the withdrawal of 
the 40000 syrian troops in lebanon 
he also refuses to recognize hrawis election to implement the 
peace plan 
geagea has recognized hrawi and cautiously accepted the peace 
plan which calls for an equal distribution of power between 
moslems and christians 
