may 5 
grants pass ore daily courier on the hostage situation 
iranian president hashemi rafsanjani is miffed that the united 
states isnt falling over itself trying to thank him for helping 
with the release of two american hostages in the past two weeks 
the releases though are a little like a man agreeing to quit 
beating two of his neighbors 19 children hes still whipping the 
remainder 
in this case rafsanjani and the terrorists in beirut supported 
by his government are inflicting the damage while western 
countries wait for the release of 17 more hostages 
why should the united states or any of these other countries 
make a goodwill gesture to terrorists who have robbed innocent 
people of years of their lives and continue to hold them for no 
apparent reason 
rewarding countries or terrorists for the release of the 
hostages would be like paying ransom which would only encourage 
the seizing of more westerners 
at first the captors members of islamic jihad or islamic 
holy war wanted to trade their hostages for 17 comrades 
imprisoned in kuwait for bombing the us and french embassies 
there 
that deal was rejected by former president reagan long ago 
though 
