in reducing the nations enormous deficit and such caution is 
more than warranted 
there has been little or no progress in reducing the deficit 
since the huge shortfall that followed passage of the delusive 
kemproth tax cut legislation in 1981 
there are several reasons for this failure to act by our elected 
officials other than sheer irresponsibility for one thing we have 
been spared the consequences of our huge deficit because foreigners 
have been willing to borrow such large amounts in our credit 
markets 
the other is that there has been no political retribution 
wreaked by the electorate on our spendthrifts 
and so once again the responsibility remains on the president 
and congress to agree on a plan that makes real deficit cuts fine 
words wont do it there have to be real reductions in spending 
and in all probability tax increases as well 
