<TEXT>
grant b cooper an attorney who defended 
kennedy assassin sirhan b sirhan has died at age 87 
cooper died may 3 of an aortic aneurysm at the hospital of the 
good samaritan in los angeles his wife phyllis said tuesday 
a trial lawyer for more than six decades cooper continued 
practicing law from his home until his death mrs cooper said 
born in new york cooper dropped out of high school and held 
several odd jobs before coming to california as a hired hand on an 
oil tanker he accepted an offer from a lawyer uncle to go into 
that profession and enrolled at southwestern university he 
graduated in 1926 and passed the state bar of california the next 
year 
as a prosecutor cooper won death penalties in several murder 
cases as a criminal defense attorney later in his career he 
opposed capital punishment claiming it did not deter murder 
coopers most notorious clients were dr r bernard finch in 
1959 and sirhan a decade later 
he obtained two hung juries for finch who was accused with his 
assistant carole tregoff of killing his wife barbara in a case 
that attracted national attention finch and tregoff were convicted 
when another attorney took over the defense in a third trial 
sirhan was convicted of the 1968 california primary election 
night slaying of sen robert kennedy at the ambassador hotel and 
remains in prison 
in addition to his second wife cooper is survived by two 
daughters from a first marriage and one daughter and two sons from 
his second marriage 
</TEXT>
</DOC>

