faster collor 40 said during a morning meeting with his 
cabinet ministers 
he also said he wanted to move more quickly on his program to 
privatize state companies and slash federal spending to wipe out a 
31 billion deficit 
collor announced a package of austerity measures on march 16 
his first full day in office as the countrys first freely elected 
president in 29 years they included closing 23 federal companies 
foundations and institutes and an 18month freeze on 115 billion 
in individual and corporate bank accounts 
but collor said wednesday there was still much to be done to 
spur growth in the economy the largest in latin america 
the president who estimated 16 million people work for the 
government or for governmentcontrolled firms ordered his 
ministers to reduce personnel by 20 percent to 25 percent 
the cuts would be made by firings and by placing excess workers 
on what is called in availability a brazilian legal term that 
means that civil servants stay at home and draw only partial 
salaries the premise is that eventually they will become disgusted 
and quit 
but collor did not give a deadline for the layoffs or explain 
how he would skirt a constitutional clause that prevents the firing 
of any federal employee who has been on the job more than five 
years 
he also said public employee salaries should be adequate for 
the reality of the national economy with special attention paid to 
intermediate and upperlevel pay this was interpreted as a sign 
that salaries will be reduced 
in assessing the initial results of his austerity program the 
president said available indicaors show inflation near zero with 
the real value of salaries increased 
before his reforms were put into effect inflation was racing 
along at a rate of 84 percent per month and totaled 4854 percent 
the past 12 months 
collor said the longterm success of the plan depended on 
reducing brazils large state sector 
