<TEXT>
in an effort to loosen ties to the east 
bloc hungarys secondlargest political party on wednesday asked 
the government to declare its intention to leave the warsaw pact 
and become a militarily neutral nation 
the league of free democrats in making its proposal to 
parliament cited a 1956 government statement that annulled 
hungarys membership in the sovietled bloc the statement prompted 
a soviet invasion that crushed the rebellion 
deputy parliament speaker matyas szueroes said the proposal 
would be discussed at the lawmaking bodys next session 
until now hungarys leadership has pledged that it would remain 
in the sovietled alliance although individual leaders have 
repeatedly suggested the country could one day become neutral 
the free democrats proposal said hungary should make clear that 
it does not wish to belong to either the warsaw pact or the western 
military alliance nato 
the party which won the secondlargest number of seats in 
parliament in april elections proposed the new declaration on the 
basis of the 1956 statement 
the proposal was presented by miklos vasarhelyi an associate of 
imre nagy the leader of the 1956 uprising vasarhelyi who was 
imprisoned following the uprising helped draft the declaration 
three days after hungary declared its withdrawal from the 
alliance soviet troops and tanks rolled into budapest to crush the 
revolt nagy was executed following a show trial 
kremlin troops have remained in hungary since then now with 
the countrys transition to democracy hungary has negotiated the 
complete withdrawal of soviet troops from her territory by the 
middle of next year 
the new parliament would like to see the accord negotiated by 
the outgoing socialist government renegotiated to speed the 
pullout a special subcommittee of the foreign relations committee 
in parliament is to deal specifically with this issue 
vasarhelyi made clear the proposal does not call for hungarys 
immediate withdrawal from the warsaw pact but opens negotiations on 
the topic with moscow 
he said if the proposal is adopted however hungary should 
suspend all activity in the east bloc alliance and forbid warsaw 
pact exercises on hungarian soil 
the new parliament is no longer dominated by communists or their 
successors the socialists in free balloting in march and april 
the socialist party gained only 33 of the 394 parliamentary seats 
jozsef antall the leader of the centerright hungarian 
democratic forum which has the most seats in parliament is trying 
to form a new government with the likeminded independent 
smallholders and the christian democrats 
