<TEXT>
billionaire adnan khashoggi claimed ownership of 
a wall street building allegedly bought by ferdinand and imelda 
marcos several months after a court order froze the marcoses 
assets a banker said wednesday 
john sanderson a citibank vice president testified that the 
representation was made by a khashoggi associate during a 
discussion in the summer of 1986 about a 39 million citibank loan 
that had been secured by the building 
sandersons testimony addressed the prosecutions allegations 
that khashoggi assumed ownership of four new york buildings held by 
the marcoses after a march 1986 injunction prohibited any transfer 
of their properties 
khashoggi a saudi financier who is charged with mail fraud and 
obstruction of justice is on trial in federal court with mrs 
marcos 
she is accused of helping her husband the late philippines 
president loot their nations treasury of more than 220 million 
using the money to support lavish living and to secretly buy the 
four buildings 
mrs marcos 60 also is charged with defrauding banks of more 
than 165 million in loans including the citibank loan to finance 
the real estate 
she has pleaded innocent to charges of racketeering 
racketeering conspiracy mail fraud and obstruction of justice 
sanderson said his initial dealings concerning the loan were 
with gliceria tantoco a close friend of mrs marcos mrs tantoco 
owner of a department store in manila also was charged in the 
indictment but is a fugitive 
sanderson testified that he had at least two meetings with mrs 
tantoco in 1984 and 1985 about problems with the wall street 
buildings management 
in july 1986 he learned that the management company was 2 
million behind in city real estate taxes and became concerned 
because any city claim would come before citibanks sanderson said 
a short time later he got a call from a karl peterson who told 
him he was working for khashoggi and said khashoggi was the 
buildings owner 
sanderson said the loan agreement had prohibited any transfer of 
the property without the banks written consent 
the bank started foreclosure on the loan in the fall of 1986 
because a substantial amount of interest and real estate taxes were 
not paid and required rehabilitation of the building was not 
undertaken sanderson said 
he left the account in the summer of 1988 but said he believed 
citibank did win a judgment and recover its money 
mrs marcos who fell ill tuesday with high blood pressure for a 
second time returned to court wednesday wearing a monitor 
shes feeling better today her attorney gerry spence said 
after the morning testimony 
