are being handed out in 1383 requests for help the federal 
emergency management agency has received since may 2 
arkansas officials say they dont know how many flood victims 
have no flood insurance only how many arkansans have it it is 
low i know that said alison mccollum of the state soil and 
water conservation commission 
as of march 31 there were 7628 flood insurance policies in 
arkansas paying premiums that totaled 1687926 said fema 
official greg solovey 
solovey said 337 areas in arkansas participate in the federal 
insurance program but some areas along the arkansas river arent 
in the program and property owners in those areas must absorb any 
losses due to flood damage 
ms mccollum said people ignore the need for flood insurance 
because they think its expensive but its not as expensive as 
people think she added 
flood insurance costs are not astronomical she said 
people should check because i know it gets out that you just 
cant afford it if people dont live in a designated flood plain 
they can get very good rates 
wanda irving who was forced by rising water to leave her home 
here said she had to get flood insurance to finance her house she 
pays 119 a year to insure the house and its contents she said 
tina mullins a sales representative said flood insurance rates 
vary but generally are inexpensive in north little rock a premium 
of 100 a year will buy 40500 worth of coverage on a house and 
1000 on contents 
the federal government underwrites all flood insurance programs 
and only those who live in cities towns or counties that 
participate in the governments national flood insurance program 
can obtain flood insurance 
to join a flood program a city or community must agree to 
certain land management goals 
in other words stop the shopping centers from building in a 
flood zone area stop the developers from putting in a residential 
area where its going to flood said bill starkey of the 
independent insurance agents of arkansas 
the federal government subsidizes flood insurance to restrict 
building in flood plains and because flood insurance never can pay 
for itself he said 
the people on the mountain top dont buy it only the ones 
next to the river starkey said 
