program would be made in 1995 said aerospatiale president henri 
martre whose company is working with british aerospace 
martre told a news conference that the companies would welcome 
us soviet west german or japanese cooperation 
british airways and air france operate 13 concordes on 
transatlantic routes the jetliners are due for retirement in 15 
to 20 years and the new planes if developed would be ready by 
about 2005 
the new generation of supersonic transport could carry about 225 
passengers over distances of up to 7500 miles at 2 times the 
speed of sound aviation experts say 
the present concorde carries 128 passengers on flights of up to 
3720 miles at twice the speed of sound 
the projected aircraft would be capable of nonstop flights 
across the pacific 
