use information obtained from foreign counterintelligence 
surveillance as evidence against the suspended diplomat in state 
department administrative proceedings 
blochs lawyers contend that the surveillances were illegal the 
justice department has asked us district judge stanley s harris 
to declare that the information was legally obtained and therefore 
can be used against bloch in the termination hearing 
