that prohibit federal workers from attending state and national 
political conventions as delegates or holding other party office 
the house version also would allow them to run for public office 
and solicit campaign funds from the public acts that would 
continue to be prohibited under the senate bill 
mcconnells amendment would have required federal employee 
unions to mail out notices annually to all 3 million government 
employees whether members of a union or not the notices would 
have to say that union members are entitled to a dues reduction 
equal to a prorata share of what the organization spends on 
political activities 
