<TEXT>
the small claims agreement 
announced wednesday opens the way for settling about 16 billion in 
claims that have been a major financial irritant between iran and 
the united states for 10 years both nations agree 
an american official and an iranian official at the iranunited 
states claims tribunal in the hague told the associated press the 
settlement will speed resolution of the big cases 
settlement of the major cases could help reestablish economic 
relations between the two nations the american official said 
the iranian official denied however that better usiran 
economic ties would result 
the economic relationship depends on the political 
relationship he said if you dont have a good relationship in 
the political sector how can you have a good relationship in the 
economic sector 
both officials spoke on condition of anonymity 
governmenttogovernment talks are expected to begin soon on 
settlement of the foreign military sales or fms claim by iran 
which the tehran government has put at about 11 billion 
the largest case before the tribunal it deals with military 
supplies ordered by shah mohammad reza pahlavi before his overthrow 
in the 1979 islamic revolution 
washington disputes tehrans figure as exaggerated claiming 
that while some of the materiel is under us embargo much of it 
was never paid for and is being held by us contractors 
the american official said once small claims are settled the 
tribunal will have more time for military equipment and oil claims 
the ninejudge arbitration panel was established as part of the 
1980 algiers accords which gained freedom for the 52 americans 
held hostage at the us embassy in tehran by iranian militants 
the tribunal has presided over the settlement of more than 22 
billion in financial disputes stemming from the iranian revolution 
resulting expropriations and broken contracts 
the oil expropriation claims filed by the american oil giants 
amoco arco and sun and by consortiums of smaller firms total 
about 5 billion 
a key to their irans economic recovery is settling all of 
them the american official said 
settlement of these cases particularly if they entailed a 
softening of us import restrictions on iranian oil would reflect 
and accelerate a thawing 
a reopening of the us oil market to iran is considered vital 
to the iranians who depend on oil exports for about 90 percent of 
their foreign exchange earnings 
theyre desperate for hard currency said the american 
official 
the small claims talks have been held almost monthly between the 
state departments chief legal adviser judge abraham sofaer and 
irans jaromi eftekhar 
sofaer is due to resign from his state department position next 
month and the american tribunal official said sofaer is expected to 
begin settlement talks before then with iran on the fms claim 
known as b1 
without the small claims the tribunal will have more 
resources to devote to b1 and the oil claims said the american 
a more speculative question is whether resolution of the 
military equipment and oil cases could provide the goodwill gesture 
sought by tehran in response to the recent release of american 
hostages robert polhill and frank reed who were held by 
proiranian shiite moslem militants in lebanon 
the american official and iran have denied any link between 
agreement on small claims and the release 
resolution of the fms and oil cases would allow the tribunal to 
shut down after almost a decade as the only official forum between 
iran and the united states which broke off diplomatic relations 
following the 1979 hostagetaking 
if we do all the things necessary to close it down doors will 
have been opened in the process said the american tribunal 
official 
it would result in improved good will 
