materialism and poverty 
john paul used the economic situation in this nation of 85 
million people as an example of the failings of capitalism 
the last few years have seen the deterioration of buying 
power and phenomena typical of the organization of the economy 
such as inflation have produced painful effects at all levels 
he said 
it is necessary to repeat once again it is always the weakest 
who suffer the worst consequences because they see themselves 
closed in a spiral of growing poverty 
mexicos economic crisis exploded in 1982 due to overborrowing 
and plunging prices for crude oil the countrys main export the 
