tie me up tie me down 
 
by turning normal values of society topsyturvy pedro almodovar 
has established himself as spains most provocative filmmaker 
women on the verge of a nervous breakdown brought him 
international acclaim and an academy award nomination for best 
foreign language picture of 1988 
almodovars new film descriptively titled tie me up tie me 
down attracted a minor storm of controversy before its release 
in this country the ratings board of the motion picture 
association of america recoiled at a graphic sex scene and dealt 
the film an x rating an appeal failed to reverse the decision now 
miramax films is releasing the film without a rating but with a 
caution about its adult material 
the rating controversy may attract those in search of sensation 
they are likely to be disappointed admirers of almodovars work 
are likely to feel the same way 
almodovars screenplay is primarily a pas de deux between 
unlikely lovers the protagonist is a handsome young mental 
patient ricky antonio banderas who manages to talk his way out 
of an asylum where he has serviced the director as well as most of 
the nurses 
ricky is obsessed with marina victoria abril a pornography 
star who is trying to become an actress in mainstream films they 
had a brief encounter during one of his escapes from the hospital 
and he is convinced she will marry him 
how to persuade marina by kidnaping her tying her up in her 
own bedroom and waiting for her to submit 
that is the essence of tie me up there is also a subplot 
about the movie marina has been making and almodovar scores some 
satiric jabs at the absurdities of the film business 
its easy to see why the ratings board decreed the x the 
lovemaking scene is depicted in graphic style and the bondage 
theme is treated lightly 
almodovar is a worldclass filmmaker and his work is replete 
with surprises tie me up is likely to rank as one of his minor 
works provocative but unrealized the saccharine ending seems 
unworthy of him 
the actors many of them seen in previous almodovar films are 
uniformly excellent both banderas and abril are skilled as well as 
attractive adding to the voltage of their eventual union 
tie me up unrated contains sex nudity and rough 
language in spanish with english subtitles running time 105 
minutes 
by bob thomas associated press writer 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
class of 1999 
</TEXT>
<TEXT>
 
the program notes for class of 1999 suggest that theres 
some kind of serious message to be gleaned from this film 
dont believe it 
class of 1999 shouldnt be taken seriously it shouldnt be 
taken as satire it shouldnt be taken any way 
the ostensible premise of this gory humorless film is that if 
you think high schools are violent today wait until the turn of 
the century 
in this nightmare world we find malcolm mcdowell playing miles 
langford principal of kennedy high school in seattle gang warfare 
has grown so pervasive that the schools surroundings have been 
declared a freefire zone where even the cops dare not go 
welcome to kennedy high school says a mechanical sounding 
voice at the school entrance all weapons must be surrendered 
before entering the school grounds 
with violent incidents occurring every two hours and 38 seconds 
on average the board of education has been renamed the department 
of educational defense 
in desperation mcdowell calls in dr bob forrest played 
nonchalantly by stacy keach sporting a graywhite rattail his 
company megatech has produced three androids who look and 
sound like teachers but who give new meaning to the word 
paddling 
at first this final solution to the student discipline 
problem seems to work some kidhating audiences may even cheer as 
these mechanical teachers forcefeed pills down the throats of 
young druggies or administer earsplitting spankings to 
foulmouthed gang members until blood oozes from their mouths 
meanwhile young cody culp a semireformed youth gang leader 
played by bradley gregg senses something vaguely inhuman about 
these teachers he vainly tries to convince langfords comely 
daughter christie that her fathers drastic cure for student 
violence just might be worse than the disease 
after a few more broken necks impalements and throat gougings 
skeptical christie is convinced that theres something faintly 
unwholesome about these new faculty members though too late to 
save the life of her father who becomes another victim of these 
androids run amok 
the hopelessly muddled plot finally has rival gang members 
putting aside their blood feud to defeat the common mechanical foe 
mark l lester produced and directed class of 1999 his 
previous credits include direction of class of 1984 another 
blackboard jungletype yarn 
in program notes lester suggests some serious message in his 
latest project that the violence plaguing schools today could 
easily lead to the horrors shown in this film unless we act to 
quell it now 
forget it if this offensive film has any message at all its 
that the producers apparently believe theres a big moviegoing 
market for wholesale violence against children 
class of 1999 is rated r richly earned because of 
almost nonstop blood guts and foul language 
by lee mitgang ap education writer 
</TEXT>
