<TEXT>
the rules are simple for the grand ole 
oprys melvin sloan dancers 
rule no 1 is to have fun rule 2 and 3 is the same rule 
says sloan 
the energetic colorful eightperson square dance troupe is 
celebrating its 10th year on the live country music show the 
group possibly the best known square dance act in the world also 
has appeared on the tv shows hee haw the nowdefunct dolly 
parton show and other programs 
the 50yearold sloan says his troupe dances a different style 
than amateur square dance clubs around the country his group 
dances to his spontaneous calls during the routine nearly all 
the local square dancers use set patterns he says 
our style is self taught he said in an interview no one 
teaches you how to do this its kind of like playing music by ear 
ours is dancing from the heart we dance like we feel you express 
yourself by moving your feet 
sloans brother ralph directed his own opry square dance group 
from 1952 until his death in 1980 melvin then took over the group 
to maintain the tradition of a sloanled opry dance troupe 
he had never danced before but he learned quickly 
i had jumped into a lake of water and i didnt know how to 
swim he recalled about his first dance steps there was 
confusion there were times wed dance and then go to the dressing 
room and cry 
he eventually mastered the art by studying patterns that other 
group members had drawn for him on paper he spent hours in front 
of a mirror in his loft perfecting the dance steps and his 
coordination 
he finally picked up where his brother left off and the group 
continued its reputation as one of the oprys most popular acts 
theres nothing that puts electricity in a crowd like a loud 
banjo and some good dancing sloan said 
the troupe ranges in age from mid20s to 50 and is recruited 
from square dance groups in tennessee no one else in the country 
dances exactly the style done in middle tennessee he said 
i tell my dancers that if you cant give me 100 percent you 
dont need to go to the stage we are always received well sloan 
said 
they perform every other weekend on the opry a fabled show that 
has been presented weekly since 1925 a million people see the 
production in person every year and millions more listen on the 
radio thirty minutes of the threehour show is carried live each 
saturday night on cable tvs the nashville network 
the sloan dancers can tell while standing behind the curtain 
just before show time whether the crowd will be responsive or 
quiet if you hear a lot of laughter and everything sounds alive 
when the curtain goes up you can feel it its a feeling of 
energy sloan said 
his group and his brothers before it boast of never having 
missed a scheduled opry performance in 38 years but melvin sloans 
troupe barely made it to a show about three years ago during an ice 
storm 
we rushed in to the opry house and didnt have time to change 
our clothes he recalled we ran out on the stage and danced in 
our street clothes to keep the streak going 
sloan designs their costumes each of the four mens attire has 
a belt and buckle shirt necktie hanky and white pants and white 
shoes these are coordinated with the womens dress apron or 
pinafore and sash hosiery and matching ties for the shoes and 
pantaloons 
the group also performs at various nashville conventions and in 
1983 at the request of then president ronald reagan they 
performed at the kennedy center for the performing arts in 
washington 
despite the tradition and the acclaim the group is not perfect 
sometimes we make a mistake sloan said but it makes me 
feel good when someone tells us it looks like we enjoy our dancing 
so much we are as proud of our dancing as any singer is of his 
singing 
