<TEXT>
fourteen states claimed victory in their effort 
to stop visa and mastercard from launching a national debit card 
and one state official hinted the vastly larger credit card market 
could be next on the states antitrust hit list 
visa usa inc and mastercard international agreed to settle 
charges brought by the states in us district court in manhattan 
last june by agreeing to abandon their joint entree debit card 
network the state attorneys general announced tuesday 
each company promised to develop separate debit card systems 
eventually 
a pointofsale debit card is presented at stores like a credit 
card but the money is deducted automatically from the cardholders 
account and transferred to the merchant 
the antitrust suit claimed entree had an unfair advantage over 
smaller regional competitors because virtually every major us 
bank already was a visa or mastercard member 
the credit card associations are the worlds largest with a 
combined 370 million cardholders 
visa and mastercard also have gained control of the nations two 
largest automatic teller machine networks cirrus system inc of 
downers grove ill and plus system inc of denver both of which 
had been formulating their own plans for national debit card 
networks since the early 1980s 
visa also took over the interlink network based in san mateo 
calif the nations largest regional debit card network 
there would have been no competitive forces at work robert 
abrams the new york attorney general who led the states action 
told a news conference the agreement doesnt prevent the concept 
from going forward it prevents a monopoly 
david brancoli a spokesman for visa disagreed we feel the 
program would have been competitive and we would have prevailed in 
the courts 
he said entree was abandoned partly because some banks had begun 
to lose interest in it in the face of what could have been a 
lengthy court battle 
the other states involved in the suit were arizona california 
connecticut louisiana maryland massachusetts minnesota 
tennessee texas utah washington west virginia and wisconsin 
at the end of 1989 there were 1839 million debit cards in 
circulation nationwide according to bankcard holders of america a 
consumer group based in herndon va but not all those cards 
operate online as entree would have by electronically 
accessing a comsumers bank account the same way as an automatic 
teller machine 
visa and mastercard began developing entree in 1986 and had 
signed up about 200 banks to participate according to richard 
woods a spokesman for mastercard two of those banks bank one of 
columbus ohio and us national bank of oregon already had 
issued around 100000 cards although none has been used he said 
under terms of the settlement signed tuesday by us district 
judge pierre n laval in manhattan visa and mastercard will 
abandon entree and notify bank participants it will be terminated 
by oct 1 in exchange the states dropped efforts to compel visa 
and mastercard to divest cirrus plus and interlink 
the speedy resolution of this complex lawsuit is the first 
important step in establishing a more competitive environment in 
the nations electornic payment systems abrams said 
he said the states agreed to set up a task force to investigate 
competition in that field particularly with credit cards 
although there are approximmatly 20000 financial institutions 
offering plastic debit credit and atm cards the interest rates 
and other fees charged is disturbingly high uniform and 
rigid said abrams 
abrams said visa and mastercard had been engaged in a creeping 
merger that already had resulted in largely uniform pricing in 
the credit card industry average credit card rates which are set 
by banks have hovered around 19 percent in recent years despite 
fluctuations in other interest rates 
david robertson a vice president for the nilson report a bank 
industry newsletter published in santa monica calif predicted 
states eventually will challenge the duality of the creditcard 
industry which allows financial institutions to be members of both 
visa and mastercard 
the competition is done with mirrors said robertson how 
can you be a member of both and remain competitive 
</TEXT>
