<TEXT>
nicaragua has resumed exports to the 
united states following former president reagans 1985 trade 
embargo sending a shipload of sugar from the port of corinto 
reagan imposed the embargo as a measure against the marxist 
sandinista government president bush lifted it after 
americanbacked violetta chamorro de barrios won the presidency in 
february elections 
nicaragua shipped 18000 metric tons of sugar on tuesday part 
of the 54328 metric tons nicaragua can sell to the united states 
this year at a preferred price above the world market 
during the embargo nicaragua sold most of its sugar a major 
export crop to soviet bloc nations 
despite tense diplomatic relations the united states remained 
the biggest buyer of nicaraguan goods until the embargo was imposed 
the us embassy which announced the shipment said the bush 
administration is considering a series of steps to reduce 
barriers and tariffs and open the market to nicaraguan exports 
other exports include cotton tobacco beef and seafood 
mrs chamorro took over a virtually bankrupt country and is 
awaiting congressional approval of 300 million in emergency 
economic aid 
