greyhound lines inc the target of a lengthy 
oftenviolent strike said wednesday it was cutting its weekday 
fares in half for two weeks beginning may 14 in an effort to lure 
back riders 
this is a business that is based on trial and then high 
repeat usage said ralph borland greyhound marketing vice 
president we want to induce them to ride and to see that the bus 
line is unencumbered 
while the promotion could mean less cash in the short term 
were in this for the long term borland said 
greyhound bus drivers walked out march 2 in a dispute over wages 
and job security but the company immediately began replacing them 
with new drivers and crossovers the strike has been marked by 
violence with buses in a number of locations hit by gunfire 
greyhound chairman fred g currey said monday that the company 
which operates the only nationwide bus system now has enough 
drivers to run at or near prestrike levels 
currey said greyhound is serving markets which provided 98 
percent of its revenue last year although ridership and revenue 
hovered around 70 percent of yearago levels not quite enough to 
meet expenses 
greyhound is offering halfprice tickets for travel monday 
through thursday in the two weeks beginning may 14 the company 
also is offering mothers day fares of 1 for travel of up to 500 
miles on sunday to mothers 18 or older 
borland said he had no projections of the fare cuts impact on 
ridership 
analysts have expressed doubts greyhound has enough cash to 
operate for the long term but company spokesman george gravley 
said we have the capacity here to run things in a reasonable 
way 
the strike has cost greyhound more than it anticipated and 
helped give the company 558 million in first quarter losses in a 
move to preserve operating funds greyhound last week said it would 
not make a 975 million interest payment due tuesday and had not 
made about 5 million in lease payments due in april 
although the missed payments open the door for creditors to take 
action to force the company into bankruptcy currey says he 
believes they will give him time to rebuild the company 
reclaiming passengers is a key to that recovery 
the typical greyhound passenger rides several times a year 
gravley said if they take one trip they generally take a lot of 
trips our job is to get them to take that first trip and then 
treat em right 
