<TEXT>
in what is believed to be the first broad offer 
of its kind one of the nations biggest advertising agencies said 
wednesday it would give clients a chance to get a guarantee on its 
work 
executives from ddb needham worldwide said the guarantee means 
the agency would get bonuses for work that produces results that 
exceed expectations and make rebates for ads that fall short 
the precise terms would vary from account to account but agency 
executives said the performance plan could increase or decrease an 
advertisers bill by as much as 30 percent 
the plan comes as advertisers are questioning the value of 
paying the standard rate that has prevailed in the ad business for 
decades without regard to performance 
an ad agency traditionally gets a 15percent cut of what an 
advertiser spends on print space or commercial air time 
there is a lot of pressure from clients for agencies to go on 
the line and be accountable for what their advertising does for the 
clients business said arthur anderson a principal in morgan 
anderson amp co an adviser to advertisers 
william weilbacher an advertising consultant said his latest 
survey for the association of national advertisers indicated only 
about a third of companies contacted last year said they pay the 
standard 15 percent rate for advertising down from about 50 
percent in a 1983 survey 
the proposal also comes as marketers are spending a greater 
portion of their budgets on activities such as package design 
sales promotion and direct mailing rather than on conventional 
advertising to the dismay of ad agencies who are paid on the basis 
of what is spent for media placements 
ddb needham was the 10th largest advertising agency based on 
worldwide billings with nearly 41 billion in 1989 according to 
the trade journal advertising age 
it produces ads for volkswagen and audi cars michelob beer 
clairol hair products ralston purina pet foods michelin tires and 
oreida potatoes 
keith l reinhard chairman and chief executive told a group of 
media representatives that the agency has been working on the 
program for more than three years 
he said it should inspire new heights of original thought and 
surprising execution because the goals are clearer and workers 
will have new incentives 
the plan works like this 
the agency and the advertiser decide on precise objectives such 
as increasing the number of customers coming into stores by a 
certain percentage or increasing consumer awareness of a brand 
the client agrees to spend a certain amount on behalf of the 
brand to integrate all of the brands marketing efforts with the 
main advertising message and to maintian the quality price and 
distribution of the product 
at the end of an agreed timeframe the results would be tallied 
and the agency would either have to pay a rebate if results came up 
short or would get a bonus if the results meet or exceed the target 
the agency would share twothirds of any bonus with employees 
who produced the improved results 
reinhard said the program has been tested with different 
clients who he declined to identify and would be made available 
first to the agencys us and canadian clients he said two have 
already said they plan to use the program the agency has 65 major 
national advertisers 
we feel confident that we have both the tools and the talent 
in hand to support this kind of guarantee he said 
several ddb needham clients such as ralston purina corp 
anheuserbusch inc and volkswagenaudi were asked for their 
reactions to the proposal but declined to comment 
industry analysts were divided on the potential impact of the 
plan for the industry in general 
they said many agencies are already working for some clients 
under compensation plans that give them bonuses for good work 
leslie winthrop the domestic president of the advertising 
agency register which matches advertisers and agencies said it 
was a very courageous thing to do for ddb needham to make the 
plan available to all clients 
she said other agencies would probably sit back and wait to 
see how it will work 
but weilbacher said ddb needhams plan is a threat to other 
agencies i dont see how an agency cannot respond to this 
gauntlet that has been thrown down he said 
</TEXT>
