<TEXT>
usx corp has fetched 25 million in an 
auction of 15 works of art in a sale that art analysts say runs 
counter to a corporate trend of buying expensive art 
the steel and energy giant has decided to sell a total of 64 
works from its 100piece collection because they can fetch a 
price said usx spokesman bill keslar 
buyers this week snatched up the 15 contemporary pieces for 
750000 more than the preauction estimate 
the market is strong for art work keslar said this was a 
privately held collection and it is like any other asset of a 
corporation 
