whose patent for an intermittent windshield wiper was violated by 
ford motor co 
us district judge avern cohns decision came after six days of 
deliberations 
the jury decided on jan 29 that ford had infringed on the 
patent held by robert w kearns but ruled tuesday that the 
infringement was not intentional limiting the amount he could be 
awarded 
tuesdays ruling meant kearns only could be awarded compensatory 
damages and not punitive damages court executive john mayer said 
the jury of five women and three men was dismissed by the judge 
who will oversee a new damages trial with new jurors 
we are disappointed the jury was unable to reach a verdict in 
damages ford spokesman tom foote said however we are pleased 
that the jury recognized that ford didnt intentionally infringe 
the kearns patents 
