annunced after top congressional leaders met with the president for 
about an hour 
foley named house majority leader richard gephardt dmo an 
outspoken critic of bush administration policies as leader of the 
house negotiating team 
i expect that were going to proceed in good faith with these 
discussions and were not going to attempt to politicize them on 
either side foley said 
some democrats have voiced concerns that the administration may 
be trying to trap them into advocating electionyear tax increases 
but foley said i trust the white house until i have reason not 
to and i have no reason not to 
foley said other house democratic negotiators are rep william 
h gray iii dpa the assistant majority leader as well as reps 
rostenkowski of illinois jamie whitten of mississippi and leon 
panetta of california the democratic chairmen of the ways and 
means appropriations and budget committees respectively 
michel of illinois named newt gingrich of georgia the assistant 
minority leader and the ranking republicans on those same three 
taxwriting and finance committees bill archer of texas silvio o 
conte of massachusetts and bill frenzel of minnesota 
