<TEXT>
producer alberto grimaldi sued time warner 
inc mgmua communications co and pathe communications corp 
wednesday claiming the three companies have entered into a 
fraudulent movie distribution deal 
the classaction suit filed in new york federal court 
maintains that pathes acquisition of mgmua and pathes subsequent 
distribution deal with time warner will deny grimaldi fees 
generated by his more 23 films in the mgmua library 
grimaldi is the producer of for a few dollars more the 
good the bad and the ugly and last tango in paris among 
other films 
he claims the deal would leave mgmua with insufficient funds to 
compensate profit participants of the films in the studios library 
pathe launched its 127 billion acquisition of mgmua in march 
in april pathe announced that time warner would provide 650 
million to help finance the acquisition 
in exchange time warner parent company of warner bros 
received distribution rights to future and current pathe and united 
artists films warner bros also is named as a defendant in the 
suit 
grimaldi an italian citizen believes time warner will receive 
an excessive share up to 75 percent of the net receipts 
generated by the exploitation of the mgmua library in his suit 
he asks that pathes deal with time warner either be rescinded or 
modified and asks for damages of not less than 50000 
grimaldi said in an interview that he is hopeful other 
filmmakers with films in the mgmua library will join him in the 
suit grimaldi said he had asked pathe to return his films to him 
but the studio declined 
i dont object to pathe buying mgmua as long as mgmua 
remains a healthy company he said 
the lawsuit alleges breach of contract interference with 
contractual relations racketeering and violations of the debtor 
and creditor law 
theodore j cohen pathes executive vice president and general 
counsel said pathe has the intention of creating a strong 
unified and viable company that will honor the obligations of all 
its constituents time warners involvement will serve to 
strengthen the enterprise 
a telephone call to time warners offices in new york was not 
answered and a phone message left with mgmua was not returned 
immediately 
