national intergroup inc said its fiscal 
fourthquarter earnings increased 26 percent in part because of 
the sale of aluminum assets 
national intergroup which owns steel drugdistribution and 
retail interests said tuesday it earned 34 million or 9 cents a 
share on sales of 7528 million in the three months ending march 
31 that was up from earnings of 27 million or 6 cents a share 
on sales of 6638 million in the yearearlier period 
national intergroup said it made 71 million in the latest 
quarter from sales of aluminum assets including the discontinued 
national aluminum interest 
the company is in the process of selling its metals business to 
concentrate on wholesale distribution primarily of 
pharmaceuticals it agreed two weeks ago to sell a 40 percent stake 
in national steel corp to nkk corp of japan for 294 million 
in the fiscal year ending march 31 national intergroup said it 
earned 557 million or 231 a share compared with a loss of 
157 million or 98 cents a share in the preceding year sales 
rose to 28 billion from 23 billion 
